C:= \prod_{j=1}^p C_j(\frac{\alpha}{p})
C_j(\alpha) = [\hat{\beta_j} - \sqrt{\tilde{\sigma^2}(X^T X)^{-1}_{jj}}t_{n-p}(\alpha/2), \hat{\beta_j} + \sqrt{\tilde{\sigma^2}(X^T X)^{-1}_{jj}}t_{n-p}(\alpha/2)]
\mathbb{P}_{\beta, \sigma^2}(\beta\in C) \geq 1-\alpha
\hat{\beta}
\hat{\beta} = (X^T X )^{-1} X^T Y
\tilde{\sigma^2} = ||(I-P)Y||^2 / (n-p)
